@untitaker Sorry for the slow response. I don't see the downside to having a separate package. If you are going to have users install RedBaron just to use the script, why not have them install the script instead? It would be easier to have a command like `flask_ext_migrate <source>.py` rather than having to directly reference the script, which requires users to first find the location of the Flask installation on their machine (right?).

Additionally, having it as a separate package will make it easy to deprecate its use, rather than having a script buried in the Flask source.

Thoughts?
